    "description": "Map the economic threshold on the lite network (realistic-economy-lite, 25 nodes) for direct comparison with targeted_sweep1 on the full network (60 nodes).\nThe original targeted_sweep5 run was fully invalidated by the role-name bug in 2_build_configs.py \u2014 economic_split was never applied to lite network nodes. This is the corrected re-run using the fixed build script.\nFixed parameters are identical to targeted_sweep1 to enable apples-to-apples comparison. pool_committed_split is fixed at 0.35 (the baseline value used across most targeted sweeps) to produce a single comparable column from the targeted_sweep1 2D grid.\nExpected comparison:\n  targeted_sweep1 (full, commit=0.35): econ=0.35\u2192v26, 0.50\u2192v26, 0.60\u2192v26,\n                                        0.70\u2192v26, 0.82\u2192v27\n  targeted_sweep5 (lite, commit=0.35): run to find out\n\nIf the lite network is a valid proxy, outcomes should match targeted_sweep1. Any divergence indicates a structural difference between the two networks beyond just node count.\n",
